00:31:30,112 --> 00:31:31,633
technology otherwise?

500
00:31:32,533 --> 00:31:34,115
Sorry, I had problems understanding it.

501
00:31:34,955 --> 00:31:37,277
Flash as your development platform, good, bad?

502
00:31:39,542 --> 00:31:45,723
Yeah, so I think Flash, I think every platform has its place. I think it depends a lot on what kind of game you want to write.

503
00:31:47,824 --> 00:31:56,467
If you want to write a game that really takes advantage of the internet and people can like share with each other and you know.

504
00:31:57,170 --> 00:32:02,811
I think in a lot of ways the way you actually win in game development is to go into the

505
00:32:02,851 --> 00:32:03,351
wilderness.

506
00:32:03,851 --> 00:32:07,712
And so don't do what I'm telling you to do and don't do what anyone here is telling you

507
00:32:07,732 --> 00:32:10,953
to do because other people are already doing that and they're already trying that.

508
00:32:11,373 --> 00:32:15,835
What you should really do is find something that you think is going to work, an idea that

509
00:32:15,875 --> 00:32:20,216
you have that other people maybe aren't having, and really try to own that and make that work.

510
00:32:21,982 --> 00:32:25,965
It's hard for me to say Flash is good and download games are bad.

511
00:32:26,205 --> 00:32:28,066
Download games convert really well,

512
00:32:28,366 --> 00:32:32,169
and people make a living off of download games.

513
00:32:32,789 --> 00:32:34,850
And Flash games have the weakness

514
00:32:34,890 --> 00:32:37,172
that single-player experiences in Flash

515
00:32:37,212 --> 00:32:38,793
probably don't convert as well.

516
00:32:40,194 --> 00:32:42,555
But you have big advantages if you're creative.

517
00:32:43,116 --> 00:32:45,457
And I think that's the real win of Flash.

