00:34:00,206 --> 00:34:00,907
hundreds of hours.

541
00:34:01,527 --> 00:34:04,908
And so, I mean, it's hard to know if that's a mistake or not.

542
00:34:04,968 --> 00:34:09,230
Now it feels a little like a mistake, and I'm not going to be doing, I'm not going

543
00:34:09,250 --> 00:34:11,771
to be pushing that much free gameplay in the next versions.

544
00:34:17,514 --> 00:34:19,915
Hi Colin, I'm Ryan from Untold Entertainment.

545
00:34:20,215 --> 00:34:20,575
Hey Ryan.

546
00:34:20,616 --> 00:34:21,156
Love your game.

547
00:34:21,516 --> 00:34:23,938
I was wondering, when you went with PayPal as your payment option,

548
00:34:24,218 --> 00:34:27,019
were you worried that you were leaving a big pile of money on the table

549
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:29,521
because PayPal doesn't cover everyone on the planet?

550
00:34:29,841 --> 00:34:32,083
This is a nice non-language based game.

551
00:34:32,643 --> 00:34:33,844
Yeah, I think...

552
00:34:34,484 --> 00:34:38,327
So, part of being like a real indie developer

553
00:34:38,747 --> 00:34:42,189
and doing it all yourself is you're wearing a lot of hats.

554
00:34:42,749 --> 00:34:43,150
And so...

555
00:34:44,054 --> 00:34:48,256
With Fantastic Contraption, the developer hat is fun to wear and the designer hat is

