00:35:41,074 --> 00:35:42,674
A huge number of people.

572
00:35:42,914 --> 00:35:47,016
And PayPal works really poorly in Taiwan.

573
00:35:47,076 --> 00:35:50,198
And so I didn't manage to monetize any of that traffic,

574
00:35:50,738 --> 00:35:52,819
which is just an absolute shame.

575
00:35:53,359 --> 00:35:56,360
On the other hand, I know people in companies

576
00:35:56,400 --> 00:36:01,362
that my wife implements payment methods professionally.

577
00:36:01,683 --> 00:36:02,503
Like, that's her job.

578
00:36:03,083 --> 00:36:06,645
And I mean, that's like a never ending.

579
00:36:07,207 --> 00:36:12,030
You could do that for your entire life. You could implement payment methods. So for me it was just

580
00:36:12,050 --> 00:36:16,873
take, you know, the biggest, easiest implement one and forget about it. I think there are like

581
00:36:16,913 --> 00:36:24,398
interesting things going on now with the kind of the flash portals implementing like payment

582
00:36:24,418 --> 00:36:29,361
methods and like aggregating them as well as like other payment aggregators. And I think

583
00:36:29,381 --> 00:36:32,963
they're really worth looking at. I don't think I

584
00:36:33,552 --> 00:36:35,892
I really haven't, I don't know how compelling it is.

585
00:36:36,052 --> 00:36:38,193
So it's really easy math to do if you should use one of those

586
00:36:38,253 --> 00:36:40,154
or if you should just like be dumb and use PayPal, right?

587
00:36:40,514 --> 00:36:42,055
So PayPal takes on a $10 purchase,

588
00:36:42,075 --> 00:36:44,555
they take like what, like 10% off the top, 10 or 15%

589
00:36:44,695 --> 00:36:47,777
depending on if it's like an American or foreign purchase.

590
00:36:48,317 --> 00:36:49,837
Oh, well, I'm Canadian,

591
00:36:49,857 --> 00:36:51,118
so I shouldn't really use the word foreign

592
00:36:51,158 --> 00:36:53,158
if it's an American or non-American purchase.

593
00:36:54,500 --> 00:36:56,961
And so payment gateways often take like 30%.

594
00:36:57,802 --> 00:37:01,004
And so if you have to get 20% more traffic from them

595
00:37:01,044 --> 00:37:01,804
to make that worth it.

596
00:37:02,165 --> 00:37:04,426
And so I haven't seen any of them

597
00:37:04,466 --> 00:37:06,808
make a really compelling argument that that's true.

598
00:37:06,848 --> 00:37:08,629
If you ask them, they'll say, oh, yeah, absolutely.

599
00:37:08,669 --> 00:37:10,650
There's like slam dunk, no problem.

600
00:37:11,030 --> 00:37:11,871
But it's hard.

601
00:37:11,891 --> 00:37:15,813
I mean, really, you need to have someone sell a game

602
00:37:15,853 --> 00:37:17,655
through PayPal and then say, oh, you know what?

603
00:37:17,675 --> 00:37:18,315
I'm not going to do that.

604
00:37:18,355 --> 00:37:19,736
I'm going to change to an aggregator

