00:37:25,935 --> 00:37:33,197
Because they could share both levels they made themselves or solutions.

608
00:37:45,145 --> 00:38:13,450
So, anybody, you don't have to pay any money to share solutions with each other. And if you buy the game, you get a level editor and you can build levels. And so, a shockingly few amount of people actually used the level editor. Andy, do you remember the... Right, so it was like under 5% of people who bought the game actually used and saved a significant, like more than one or two levels. And so,

609
00:38:15,139 --> 00:38:21,642
The level sharing was, uh, the level sharing didn't take, it wasn't nearly as valuable as the contraption sharing.

610
00:38:21,682 --> 00:38:24,064
I mean, uh, there's a couple of reasons for that, I think.

611
00:38:24,644 --> 00:38:29,966
Uh, one, the level creation is, uh, isn't as show-offy as building contraptions.

612
00:38:30,107 --> 00:38:36,890
And people are, like, users are much more interested in showing off how smart they are than, um, how well they can design a level.

613
00:38:37,330 --> 00:38:42,493
So if you look like, uh, yeah, if you look at this level, like, this is one of my levels, it's like, very simple.

614
00:38:43,087 --> 00:38:44,588
It's just a bunch of stairs.

615
00:38:44,909 --> 00:38:47,731
And as a level designer, the idea

616
00:38:47,771 --> 00:38:49,031
behind my level design and contraption

617
00:38:49,091 --> 00:38:50,693
was to get out of the way as much as I can

618
00:38:50,733 --> 00:38:52,634
so that the user can have all the fun.

619
00:38:52,954 --> 00:38:54,575
Contraption is not about me being smart.

620
00:38:54,655 --> 00:38:55,696
It's about you being smart.

621
00:38:56,276 --> 00:39:00,179
And so when a good level is not about the designer looking

622
00:39:00,259 --> 00:39:02,321
smart, I mean, obviously, you have to be smart to make it

623
00:39:02,421 --> 00:39:05,683
look very simple and elegant.

624
00:39:06,203 --> 00:39:08,785
But when it's not obvious that you're being smart,

625
00:39:08,805 --> 00:39:10,066
then people just don't really care.

626
00:39:10,466 --> 00:39:11,447
And so.

627
00:39:12,290 --> 00:39:16,871
The levels people actually make end up being oddly overcomplicated and doing funny things

628
00:39:16,951 --> 00:39:18,152
and are very little fun to play.

629
00:39:18,312 --> 00:39:24,873
So I would say the level sharing was fairly uninteresting from a point both of levels

630
00:39:24,893 --> 00:39:27,774
that were created as well as traffic that it actually brought in.

631
00:39:30,755 --> 00:39:35,376
And I think that using users to actually make...

632
00:39:36,702 --> 00:39:41,704
We've experimented with having contests add levels to the games and trying to offload

