00:40:54,712 --> 00:40:57,233
They're not just like trying to make you feel good.

657
00:40:57,933 --> 00:40:59,453
And in terms of user testing,

658
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:05,181
I've done a ton of testing more recently for a game in the kind of contraption universe.

659
00:41:29,159 --> 00:41:34,344
And it's kind of a lot more traditional puzzle game

660
00:41:34,404 --> 00:41:36,365
with kind of traditional answers and solutions.

661
00:41:36,826 --> 00:41:38,887
And so especially when you're not

662
00:41:38,928 --> 00:41:40,149
working with something as open-ended

663
00:41:40,209 --> 00:41:42,070
as Fantastic Interaction, user testing

664
00:41:42,150 --> 00:41:45,033
is just unbelievably important.

665
00:41:46,254 --> 00:41:48,856
I cannot stress enough how important user testing is.

666
00:41:49,601 --> 00:41:54,742
A puzzle may seem really easy to you and they may be completely impossible to the user.

667
00:41:55,342 --> 00:41:59,243
And you may be, okay, well, all I need to do is move the ball like four pixels to the

668
00:41:59,283 --> 00:42:00,623
right and everything will be obvious.

669
00:42:01,203 --> 00:42:05,504
And that may be true, but by moving that thing four pixels to the right, you accomplish that

670
00:42:05,524 --> 00:42:08,165
goal and then lose them on something totally different.

671
00:42:08,585 --> 00:42:11,466
So you can never really make changes and then consider a level solved.

672
00:42:11,486 --> 00:42:16,847
You have to make changes, iterate, get somebody to test it, and then make changes and test,

673
00:42:16,887 --> 00:42:17,687
changes and test.

674
00:42:17,787 --> 00:42:18,887
And so you just have to run through.

675
00:42:19,357 --> 00:42:20,317
A lot of testers.

676
00:42:20,697 --> 00:42:23,878
And of course that's hard because you run out of people, especially in your target demographic.

677
00:42:23,898 --> 00:42:25,938
You get people who are too good at games or too bad at games.

678
00:42:26,618 --> 00:42:29,439
But yeah, the only way to do it is to just say nothing.

679
00:42:30,199 --> 00:42:34,000
They'll turn to you and ask for help all the time and you just have to ignore them and

680
00:42:34,020 --> 00:42:35,020
say no, I'm not going to help you.

681
00:42:35,400 --> 00:42:39,641
Actually, one really good tactic that testers use is they'll start up a puzzle and they'll

682
00:42:39,681 --> 00:42:43,361
say they'll play at it for a while and then they'll go, oh man, all right, I give up.

683
00:42:43,942 --> 00:42:44,482
How do you do it?

684
00:42:45,162 --> 00:42:46,182
And then you say, oh, what?

685
00:42:46,322 --> 00:42:47,142
I don't know.

686
00:42:47,222 --> 00:42:47,462
Maybe.

687
00:42:48,593 --> 00:42:49,854
I'm not going to tell you how to do it.

688
00:42:49,894 --> 00:42:50,834
It's like, that would be cheating.

689
00:42:51,235 --> 00:42:53,096
And then they immediately go back to trying to solve it.

690
00:42:54,116 --> 00:42:56,818
Like it was their tactic to try to get through

691
00:42:56,878 --> 00:42:57,739
having to not solve it.

692
00:42:59,300 --> 00:42:59,640
Thank you.

